@peterjc123 Looks like the error is caused because there are two different dispatch_hash functions with identical signatures defined:

template<typename T>
auto dispatch_hash(const T& o) -> decltype(std::hash<T>()(o), std::size_t()) {
  return std::hash<T>()(o);
}

and

template<typename T>
auto dispatch_hash(const T& o) -> decltype(T::hash(o), std::size_t()) {
  return T::hash(o);
}

I can see why this would confuse the compiler, as it is not immediately clear which version would receive the call from line 75. Commenting out the bottom function fixes the error and everything compiles successfully all the way to the end, however, I doubt that is the proper fix.
